{"word":"ἐφήμερος","slug":"ἐφήμερος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐφήμερος</b></el> <el>(ἐφ-ήμερος, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἡμέρα'><el>ἡμέρα</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>living but a day, short-lived</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of men, <el>ἐφήμεροι</el> <i>creatures of a day</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>for the day, daily</i>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><el>φάρμακον ἐφ.</el> <i>killing on the same day</i>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}